  • Method Details

    • isAtTarget

      public boolean isAtTarget()
      Checks if the motor is at the target setpoint. If the motor is being controlled in velocity control mode, the absolute difference between the current velocity and the target velocity is checked against the tolerance. If the motor is being controlled in position control mode, the absolute difference between the current position and the target position is checked against the tolerance. If the motor is being controlled in duty cycle control mode, the function returns false.
      Returns:
      true if the motor is at the target setpoint, false otherwise.

    • setValues

      public void setValues(GenericPID pid)
      Sets the PID configuration values for the TalonFX motor.

      This function will take the PID values and apply them to the TalonFX motor. The kP, kI, kD, and kS constants are set using the TalonFXConfigurator class.

      Parameters:
      pid - the PID values to set.

    • configureAbsoluteControl

      public void configureAbsoluteControl(double offset, boolean inverted, double min, double max)
      Configure the PID controller for absolute control. This is the same as absolute encoder control, but for the TalonFX.
      Parameters:
      offset - The offset of the absolute position sensor.
      inverted - Whether the sensor is inverted or not.
      min - The minimum position value.
      max - The maximum position value.
